{%- comment -%}
  Product Form — quantity + add to cart + dynamic checkout button.
  Birebir from source PDP: quantity selector + ATC + wishlist/share.
  Uses Shopify {% form 'product' %} with variant ID.

  Accepts:
  - product:              {Object}  Shopify product
  - show_dynamic_checkout {Boolean} render the Shop Pay / Buy it now button.
                                    Defaults to true (Theme Store best practice).
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign current_variant = product.selected_or_first_available_variant -%}
{%- if show_dynamic_checkout == nil -%}
  {%- assign show_dynamic_checkout = true -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Wrapping div carries the `data-product-form` selector hook and the
  product id so product-form.js can find the form without relying on
  hyphenated kwargs inside the `{% form %}` tag — Liquid's kwarg parser
  accepts `data-*: value` via a Shopify-specific extension, but passing
  empty strings (`data-product-form: ''`) is brittle and some linters
  flag the hyphens as arithmetic tokens. A plain <div> wrapper keeps
  the selector hooks out of Liquid-tag territory entirely.
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="kt-product-form" data-product-form data-product-id="{{ product.id }}">
{%- form 'product', product, id: 'ProductForm' -%}
  <input type="hidden" name="id" value="{{ current_variant.id }}" data-variant-id>

  {%- comment -%}
    Gift card recipient form — only rendered when the product being
    purchased is itself a gift card (Shopify's product.gift_card?
    object). When set, the customer can opt in to emailing the
    issued card directly to a recipient on a scheduled date.
    Required for any store that sells digital gift cards — Theme
    Store flags the absence as a missing mandatory feature.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- if product.gift_card? -%}
    {%- render 'gift-card-recipient-form', product: product, form: form, section: section -%}
    <script src="{{ 'gift-card-recipient.js' | asset_url }}" defer="defer"></script>
  {%- endif -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    Quantity-rule resolution. Merchants can now declare a
    variant-level quantity rule via admin → Product → Variants →
    Quantity rules (min / max / increment, e.g. "sold in packs of 6").
    Shopify exposes these via `variant.quantity_rule.{min,max,increment}`
    — all three default to sensible integers (1/nil/1) when the
    merchant hasn't configured them, so this logic is safe for every
    product.

    Without respecting the rule:
      - A case-of-6 item renders `min=1 step=1 value=1` and every
        add-to-cart fails with "Quantity must be a multiple of 6."
      - A max-500 bulk variant can be over-ordered; Shopify rejects
        silently at checkout.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign qty_min = current_variant.quantity_rule.min | default: 1 -%}
  {%- assign qty_step = current_variant.quantity_rule.increment | default: 1 -%}
  {%- assign qty_max = current_variant.quantity_rule.max -%}

  {%- comment -%} Quantity + Add to Cart row {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="kt-product-form__row">
    {%- comment -%} Quantity selector {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="kt-product-form__qty">
      <button type="button" class="kt-product-form__qty-btn" data-qty-minus aria-label="{{ 'kt.product.quantity.decrease' | t: title: product.title }}">
        <svg aria-hidden="true" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line></svg>
      </button>
      <input
        type="number"
        name="quantity"
        id="Quantity-{{ product.id }}"
        value="{{ qty_min }}"
        min="{{ qty_min }}"
        step="{{ qty_step }}"
        {% if qty_max != blank %}max="{{ qty_max }}"{% endif %}
        inputmode="numeric"
        pattern="[0-9]*"
        class="kt-product-form__qty-input"
        data-qty-input
        data-qty-min="{{ qty_min }}"
        data-qty-step="{{ qty_step }}"
        {% if qty_max != blank %}data-qty-max="{{ qty_max }}"{% endif %}
        aria-label="{{ 'kt.product.quantity.label' | t }}"
      >
      <button type="button" class="kt-product-form__qty-btn" data-qty-plus aria-label="{{ 'kt.product.quantity.increase' | t: title: product.title }}">
        <svg aria-hidden="true" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"></line><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line></svg>
      </button>
    </div>

    {%- comment -%}
      Add to Cart button — two icons rendered, CSS swaps based on :disabled.

      Also disabled when the product REQUIRES a selling plan
      (subscription-only item with no one-time-purchase path). Without
      this gate, the ATC posts to /cart/add without a `selling_plan`
      param and Shopify rejects with a generic error. Gate here so the
      customer sees a clear disabled state + localised "Subscription
      required" copy instead.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- assign atc_disabled = false -%}
    {%- unless current_variant.available -%}{%- assign atc_disabled = true -%}{%- endunless -%}
    {%- if product.requires_selling_plan -%}{%- assign atc_disabled = true -%}{%- endif -%}
    <button
      type="submit"
      class="kt-product-form__atc"
      {% if atc_disabled %}disabled{% endif %}
      data-add-to-cart
    >
      {%- comment -%} Available: shopping bag icon {%- endcomment -%}
      <svg class="kt-product-form__atc-icon kt-product-form__atc-icon--available" aria-hidden="true" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
        <path d="M6 2L3 6v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V6l-3-4z"></path>
        <line x1="3" y1="6" x2="21" y2="6"></line>
        <path d="M16 10a4 4 0 0 1-8 0"></path>
      </svg>
      {%- comment -%} Sold out: X-in-circle icon {%- endcomment -%}
      <svg class="kt-product-form__atc-icon kt-product-form__atc-icon--sold-out" aria-hidden="true" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
        <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
        <line x1="15" y1="9" x2="9" y2="15"></line>
        <line x1="9" y1="9" x2="15" y2="15"></line>
      </svg>
      <span data-add-to-cart-text>
        {%- if product.requires_selling_plan -%}
          {{ 'kt.product.subscription_required' | t }}
        {%- elsif current_variant.available -%}
          {{ 'kt.product.add_to_cart' | t }}
        {%- else -%}
          {{ 'kt.product.sold_out' | t }}
        {%- endif -%}
      </span>
    </button>
  </div>

  {%- if product.requires_selling_plan -%}
    {%- comment -%}
      Subscription-only products can't be bought one-time. Render a
      short explanatory hint so the customer understands why the ATC
      is disabled. Full selling-plan picker UX is deferred — when it
      ships, this block will render the picker instead of the hint.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <p class="kt-product-form__subscription-hint" role="note">
      {{ 'kt.product.subscription_required_hint' | t }}
    </p>
  {%- endif -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    Error sentinel — populated by product-form.js when /cart/add.js
    responds with an error (out of stock, quantity limit, network).
    Hidden by default; JS toggles [hidden] and fills textContent.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="kt-product-form__error" data-product-form-error role="alert" hidden></div>

  {%- comment -%} Dynamic Checkout Button (Buy Now / Shop Pay etc.) {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- if show_dynamic_checkout -%}
    <div class="kt-product-form__dynamic-checkout">
      {{ form | payment_button }}
    </div>
  {%- endif -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    Wishlist + Share — real, privacy-safe implementations.
    Wishlist persists product handles in localStorage (no server, no cookies).
    Share uses the Web Share API with a clipboard fallback. No tracking.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="kt-product-form__actions">
    <button
      type="button"
      class="kt-product-form__action-btn"
      data-wishlist-toggle
      data-product-handle="{{ product.handle }}"
      data-product-title="{{ product.title | escape }}"
      aria-pressed="false"
      data-label-add="{{ 'kt.product.wishlist' | t }}"
      data-label-added="{{ 'kt.product.wishlist_added' | t }}"
    >
      <svg aria-hidden="true" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
        <path d="M20.84 4.61a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 0L12 5.67l-1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 7.78l1.06 1.06L12 21.23l7.78-7.78 1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0 0-7.78z"></path>
      </svg>
      <span data-wishlist-label>{{ 'kt.product.wishlist' | t }}</span>
    </button>
    <button
      type="button"
      class="kt-product-form__action-btn"
      data-share-btn
      data-share-title="{{ product.title | escape }}"
      data-share-url="{{ shop.url }}{{ product.url }}"
      data-label-default="{{ 'kt.product.share' | t }}"
      data-label-copied="{{ 'kt.product.share_copied' | t }}"
    >
      <svg aria-hidden="true" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
        <circle cx="18" cy="5" r="3"></circle>
        <circle cx="6" cy="12" r="3"></circle>
        <circle cx="18" cy="19" r="3"></circle>
        <line x1="8.59" y1="13.51" x2="15.42" y2="17.49"></line>
        <line x1="15.41" y1="6.51" x2="8.59" y2="10.49"></line>
      </svg>
      <span data-share-label>{{ 'kt.product.share' | t }}</span>
    </button>
  </div>
{%- endform -%}
</div>
